  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building the Social Cohesion of Communities Receiving Youth Returnees as a Bridge to Peaceful and Effective Reintegration</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project promotes an integrated and territorial approach to conflict prevention and the effective reintegration of returnee youth in the municipalities of Tacan&#xE1; and Concepci&#xF3;n Tutuapa, San Marcos, Guatemala. The project will strengthen the capacities of local and national government. It will strengthen youth leadership through educational programs and promote participation in decision-making platforms in their communities, facilitating their social, cultural and political reintegration. Through the &#x201C;Conflict Prevention and Stability&#x201D; strategy that will invest in productive technical training; adoption of sustainable agricultural practices that reduce climate impact; diversification towards non-agricultural activities, effective rural services and investments in value chains; training for the labor market; decent rural employment opportunities for returnees such as those in receiving communities; inclusion and access to financial resources for women and youth. The project will be innovative, addressing emerging conflict through prevention strategies, and returnees will become crucial agents of change.</narrative>
  </description>
